# Server vs Client Components

- Default to Server Components. Add `'use client'` only when a file actually
  needs interactivity, browser APIs, hooks, or the WebSocket connection.
- Data-heavy read-only pages (workspace list, project list, dashboard) fetch
  data directly in the Server Component — no client-side `useEffect` fetch
  for initial page data.
- The Kanban board itself is a Client Component (drag state, WebSocket,
  optimistic updates) — but its outer page shell (layout, header) stays a
  Server Component wrapping it.

# Folder structure

```
frontend/
  app/
    (auth)/login/  (auth)/register/
    workspace/[id]/page.tsx
    workspace/[id]/project/[projectId]/page.tsx
    workspace/[id]/analytics/page.tsx
  components/
    board/          # Kanban board, columns, cards (client)
    dashboard/       # chart components (client, receive data as props)
    ui/               # small reusable primitives (button, input, badge)
  lib/
    api-client.ts     # typed fetch wrapper to the NestJS API
    socket.ts          # Socket.io client singleton + typed event map
    auth.ts             # token/session helpers
  store/
    board-store.ts      # Zustand store for board UI state
```

# State management

- Zustand only for client-side UI state that multiple components need
  (board drag state, optimistic task positions). Don't put server data that
  belongs to a single page in a global store — pass it down as props or fetch
  it locally.
- Optimistic updates: on drag end, update the Zustand store immediately, fire
  the API call, and on failure roll back to the last known-good state with a
  visible toast/error — never fail silently (see PROJECT_PLAN.md Phase 5
  "Hunt for").

# Data fetching & types

- All API calls go through `lib/api-client.ts` — no raw `fetch()` calls
  scattered in components.
- Define request/response types in one place per domain
  (`lib/types/task.ts`, etc.) and import them on both the API client and the
  components — do not duplicate shape definitions.
- The refresh-token flow (401 → refresh → retry) lives in the API client as
  an interceptor-style wrapper, not repeated per call site.

# Styling

- Tailwind CSS utility classes for layout/spacing. Keep component-specific
  complex styling in the component file, not scattered global CSS.
- No inline style objects for anything expressible in Tailwind.

# Realtime

- One Socket.io client instance (`lib/socket.ts`), connected once per
  workspace the user is viewing, disconnected on unmount.
- On reconnect (the socket's `connect` event firing again after a drop),
  refetch the current board state rather than assuming no events were missed
  — see PROJECT_PLAN.md Phase 4 "Hunt for".
